parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the regenerative braking system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potential fatalities.
symptoms: The transition from regenerative braking to mechanical braking is sloppy and abrupt
causing the ABS system to activate as the wheels suddenly lock up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potential fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
sticks to the floor
or has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of air bags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, compromising the safety of vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Air bags do not deploy immediately or at all in the event of a crash
delayed deployment of air bags
air bag warning messages or error codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays or inadequate responses to recalls can put vehicle owners at risk of accidents or injuries due to unresolved safety issues.
symptoms: Long wait times for recall repairs
lack of urgency in addressing safety issues
inadequate communication from manufacturers or dealerships.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and elevated RPM can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents. The issue can also cause the check engine warning light to illuminate, which may indicate a more serious problem.
symptoms: The transmission is slipping
the RPM is elevated
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the cruise control is not operating correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the clutch can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
